logical vectors

A logical vector is a vector that only contains TRUE and FALSE (and also NA) values. In R, true values are designated with TRUE, and false values with FALSE. logicals are very usefull for indexing other vectors.

x <- c(TRUE, TRUE , FALSE)

y <- c(TRUE, FALSE, FALSE)
